programme.desc: Buzz finds a new friend at the playground, Jojo makes waka rererangi and Tama, Maia & Jojo have friends round for tea.

programme.title: Aussie Bush Tales
programme.desc: The children go down to the Paperbark Billabong hoping to see the strange creature which the Elder Moort tells them lives in the water. Moort describes the noise made by the creature as 'Baoloo-oo'.

programme.title: Bushwhacked
programme.desc: A matchmaking mission that takes Kayne and Kamil to Lake Eyre and Cooper Pedy, but far from romantic, this adventure involves the world's most venomous snake!

programme.title: Fresh Fairytales

programme.title: The Magic Canoe
programme.desc: Nico insists a lot that we play with him and it is only in the funny adventure that he will understand that people sometimes have other things to do than having fun with us.

programme.title: Motown Magic
programme.desc: Imaginative boy Ben transforms his city by bringing colorful street art to life, armed with a magic paintbrush and the classic sounds of Motown.

programme.title: Spartakus And The Sun Beneath The Sea
programme.desc: Audio Described (AD). A ship without sails, adrift, an unconscious passenger... this navigator is rescued by our hero is Ulysses!

programme.title: Waabiny Time
programme.desc: There are maar keny bonar, six seasons. Birak is hot time, time for djiba-djobaliny, swimming time.

programme.title: Wolf Joe
programme.desc: When a new playmate arrives, Nina becomes increasingly competitive but finds she's not the best at everything.

programme.title: The World According To Grandpa
programme.desc: Connie asks 'Who discovered fire?' and Grandpa spins a tall tale about Priscilla Von Wow, a stone-age magician who needed to think of the most spectacular magic trick the world had ever seen!
